{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Polenta","content":["Preheat oven to 180°C. Line a baking tray (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper.","Remove stalks from mushrooms and discard. Place mushrooms onto prepared tray, gill side up. If any of the mushrooms do not sit flat, remove a small slice from the bottom of the mushroom. Set baking tray with mushrooms aside.","Place water, milk, oil, bay leaves, thyme and stock paste into mixing bowl and cook <b>5 min\/90°C\/speed 1<b>. Carefully remove bay leaves and discard.","Add polenta, salt and pepper and cook <b>15 min\/100°C\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then set mixture aside in mixing bowl to cool for approx. 10 minutes.","Add mascarpone and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>.","Transfer polenta into reserved mushrooms to fill and bake for 20 minutes (180°C). Clean and dry mixing bowl. Meanwhile, continue with caramelised onion and Brussels sprouts."]},{"title":"Caramelised onion and Brussels sprouts","content":["Place Brussels sprouts into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place garlic and onion into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add all remaining caramelised onion ingredients, except Brussels sprouts, and cook <b>8 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>.","Add reserved Brussels sprouts and cook <b>2 min\/Varoma\/\/speed <b>.","Garnish mushrooms with caramelised onions and Brussels sprouts before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Polenta","content":["6 fresh Portobello mushrooms","240 g water","220 g full cream milk","2 tsp olive oil","2 dried bay leaves","½ tsp dried thyme","1 tbsp Vegetable stock paste (see Tips)","100 g polenta (see Tips)","1 - 2 pinches sea salt, to taste","½ tsp ground black pepper, to taste","100 g mascarpone cheese"]},{"title":"Caramelised onion and Brussels sprouts","content":["8 Brussels sprouts, cut into halves","1 garlic clove","120 g red onion, cut into halves","20 g unsalted butter","1 tbsp soft dark brown sugar","1 tbsp balsamic vinegar","½ tsp sea salt"]}],"id":"r106376","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-4AGqrNjLp4M\/XZafbXgSTaI\/AAAAAAAAguM\/alBzPEm1-LcOYfpLUIx32iPBrE2ASPCyACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_nC0ek-l4t9BaUf0s.png","title":"Stuffed Portobello mushrooms with caramelised Brussels sprouts","publishedAt":"2016-07-18T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"9.7 g","fat":"10.9 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"17.9 g","calories":"919 kJ \/ 219 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Refer to <em>The Basic Cookbook <\/em>or <em>E<\/em><em>veryday Cookbook <\/em>for the Vegetable stock paste recipe.","We suggest using fine polenta in this reicpe, do not use the quick-cooking variety."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h","6 portions"]}